Floral baskets laid before Kim Il Sung's statues
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Working people, servicemen, schoolchildren and students across the country visited the President Kim Il Sung's statues to lay floral baskets, bouquets and flowers on July 8, the 5th anniversary of his passing away.
   Those in Pyongyang visited the President's statue on Mansu Hill.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Laid before the statue was a floral basket sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il.
   Officials and working people from party, armed forces, and  power organs, ministries, national institutions, factories, enterprises, organizations and farms, People's Army soldiers, schoolchildren and students laid floral baskets, bouquets and flowers and paid their deep respects to the statue.   Floral baskets, bouquets and flowers were also laid before the President's statues at Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung University of Politics, the Ministry of Public Security, the Korean Film Studio, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other places of Pyongyang.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the same day, working people, servicemen, schoolchildren and students in different parts of the country visited the President's statues in their residential quarters and laid floral baskets, bouquets and flowers.   meanwhile, officials of foreign embassies and missions of the international organizations, Chinese delegations and Koreans from China laid floral baskets before the President's statue on Mansu Hill on July 8, the 5th anniversary of his passing away.   members of the Chinese consulate general in Chongjin laid a floral basket before the President's statue in Chongjin on the same day.

Memorial meetings and services
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Memorial meetings and services were held in provinces, cities and counties, at industrial complexes and units of the three services of the Korean People's Army to commemorate the 5th anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present were leading officials of local party and power organs and working people's organizations, those who were received in audience by the President, those who were related to his revolutionary activities, men of meritorious services and other people and officers and men of units of the three services.   All the participants paid a silent tribute to President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speakers said that the passing away of the President five years ago brought the greatest pain in the 5,000 year long history of the  nation to our state and the greatest loss to the Korean people and the world progressive people.
   They went on:   The life of the President was the life of a great revolutionary, distinguished politician and invincible and iron-willed commander who led the revolution to victory, enjoying the absolute support and trust of the Korean people and the world revolutionary people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All the victories in the  20th century history of the country and the revolutionary movement of the popular masses are associated with his august name. The Korean revolution to which his noble life was devoted has greeted new era of upsurge under the leadership of the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il. Over the last five years  the Marshal has created an unprecedentedly great revolutionary history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He, opening a new history of the revolutionary leadership of giving priority to military affairs, continuously inspected the frontline and visited different sectors of the national economy,  strengthened the revolutionary armed forces into an invincible strong army, breaking through all difficulties and adversities by himself, and provided a firmer guarantee for the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche by laying a springboard from which to make the arduous march a cheerful march.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from O Ik Je
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from O Ik Je, vice-chairman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter said:   The wail of all the people over the passing away of the great President more clearly proved than  the history of thousands of years that there was not such a great man as him in the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is you who guarantee the eternal life of the President. Korea is a great country where  even a blade of grass and a gravel stone are associated with the eternal life of the President.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Touring different parts of the country along the course of on-the-spot guidance  taken by you the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il, I have realised that in all your activities you exerted primary effort to materialize the wishes of the President and it was their sole objective and boiled down to its realization.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   You are leading the building of a powerful nation which was wished by the President. Korea will surely rise as a powerful nation before long. The whole nation is living with the confidence of the future, looking up to you, who are called the great spirit of the nation for your great and noble aim. Your song is rocking the three thousand-ri land of the country, north and south, as a banner of patriotism.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Indeed, the prosperity of a powerful reunified country is in store as it is led by you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   I will do my duty as a member of the nation in the sacred history of advance, upholding the President forever, by devoting all my life to the sacred cause of national reunification.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Ri In Mo
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from former war correspondent  of the Korean People's Army Ri In Mo on July 8, the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's passing away.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said in his letter that he saw the image of President Kim Il Sung who was pioneering the Korean revolution on Mt. Paektu and pushing his way through all sorts of hardships in the past in Kim Jong Il who is breaking through the difficulties of the revolution, holding high the red flag.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   I was struck with admiration at the world-startling outstanding leadership of you who are defending  by yourself our country and socialism, the revolutionary heritage of the President, and guaranteeing its victorious advance. Such admiration has grown stronger over the last five years, deepening my unbounded respect and absolute worship for you. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Under your leadership,  all things are going well as wished by the President in his lifetime and his cause is bearing a shining fruition.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   I will hold you in high esteem, entrusting my destiny only to you as long as I live.

Homage paid to President Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- People of various strata and servicemen of the people's army on Thursday visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay deep homage to the President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of his passing away. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese  revolutionary fighters and KPA servicemen and Pyongyangites from all walks of life visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace yesterday. People of various social strata and KPA servicemen paid homage to the statue of the President and went upstairs to pay the deepest respects to him who lies in state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   And families and children of former Korean anti-Japanese  revolutionary fighters in China and those related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay respects to him.   The members of the delegation of the National Democratic Front of South Korea headed by chief Pak Kwang Gi of the NDFSK mission in Pyongyang and overseas compatriots went there and paid homage to him yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Delegations and figures of different countries on a visit to Korea, the foreign diplomatic corps and representatives of international organizations, military attaches corps, economic and commercial councilors corps and officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of different embassies here visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace to pay homage to him.

Central memorial service of Japan-resident Koreans held
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, July 8 (KNS-KCNA) -- A central memorial service to commemorate the 5th anniversary of the passing away of the President Kim Il Sung was held in Tokyo by Koreans in Japan on Thursday.   The service was attended by chairman Han Tok Su, first vice-chairman So Man Sul and chief vice-chairman Ho Jong Man, of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and other Chongryon officials.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Addressing the service, Han Tok Su called upon the Chongryon officials and compatriots of the new generation in Japan to firmly defend Chongryon through generations and  give momentum to the national patriotic movement, upholding  the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il with loyalty just as patriotic Koreans of the first generation in Japan absolutely revered the great leader Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   So Man Sul in a memorial address said the Japan-resident Koreans  have keenly realized hourly and daily over the past five years what a great man they  held in high esteem as their leader and what a great pain it was for the nation to be bereaved of the Generalissimo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Generalissimo created a unique ideology and theories on the movement of overseas compatriots and organized Chongryon. He devoted all his energies to strengthening and developing the Juche-oriented movement of Koreans in Japan, he said, and continued:   Since there is the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il, the Generalissimo  will live forever as the sun of Juche in the hearts of not only compatriots in the homeland but those in Japan. Thanks to the wise leadership and deep loving care of the Marshal, it was possible to firmly defend Chongryon, the patriotic legacy of the Generalissimo, and strengthen and develop the movement of Koreans in Japan.

Memorial evening on 5th death anniversary of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- A memorial evening to commemorate the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's passing away "the leader will be with us forever" was held at the Grand East Pyongyang Theatre on Thursday.  Present there were senior party and state officials Choe Thae Pok, Yang Hyong Sop, Choe Yong Rim, Kim Ki Nam, Kim Jung Rin and officials of party and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people in the city.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In a poem "President will always live in the people's hearts", the performers told about the greatness of the President who made immortal exploits for the fatherland and people, era and history by leading the revolution and construction to victory.   Performers eulogized the President who built the DPRK into the socialist fatherland of Juche and put forward the Korean people as the most dignified and happiest people in the world, singing songs including "Song of Loyalty", "Our Leader" and "We began on the ruins".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, schoolchildren's  function "poem reciting and  story-telling gathering of loyal and filial children looking up to the immortal sun forever" was held on Wednesday at the statue of President Kim Il Sung standing in front of the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace.

Senior Korean cardres meet foreign delegations
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, met and had a talk with the visiting delegation of the Foreign Ministry of Syria led by vice-Minister Suleyman Haddad at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The head of the delegation said that the Syrian people will stand firmly on the side of the Korean people who are struggling for justice, no matter how difficult the situation may be. He wished the Korean people who are united close around the great leader Kim Jong Il greater success in their struggle for socialist construction and the reunification of the country.   Foreign Minister of the DPRK Paek Nam Sun met the delegation on the same day.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Meanwhile, Kim Yong Sun, chairman of the Korean Asia-Pacific Peace Committee, met and conversed with Kanji Inoki, President of the New Japan Professional Wrestling Co. Ltd., and his party.

Sojourn of Norodom Sihanouk's entourage in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 9 (KCNA) -- Entourage of Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk on July 8 visited Mangyongdae where the President Kim Il Sung was born.   Being briefed on his glorious revolutionary history and family, the guests went with keen interest  around mementos preserved with much care.   They had a picture taken in front of the President's native home.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the end of the visit Kong Sam Ol, deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace of Cambodia, said that while visiting Mangyongdae, they were overwhelmed by boundless reverence for the President.   He added that the President will be immortal.   The guests inspected the international friendship exhibition.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After visiting the exhibition, Kong Sam Ol and Minister of State of the Royal Government and Concurrently Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation of Cambodia Hor Namhong wrote in the visitor's book that the Korean people could register excellent successes under the banner of the Juche idea thanks to the wise guidance of the great leaders  Kim Il Sung and Marshal Kim Jong Il.  
"Many gifts from foreign countries represent the trust of humankind in the Generalissimo and the Marshal."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The guests also visited the Tower of the Juche Idea, the monument to party founding, the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong, the Pyongyang Metro and other places.   They appreciated an acrobatic performance at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre.
